Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Soak the @bamboo skewers{4} in a #bowl{} of water. Trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Thinly slice the green parts of the @spring onion{4}(thinly sliced) , then chop the white part into thirds widthways. Halve the @lime{1}(halved).

Put the @soy sauce{50%ml}, @miso paste{30%g} and the @honey{15%ml} into a large bowl and mix to combine. Transfer half of the mix into a #mug{} and set aside. Returning to the large bowl, add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} into the mix and whisk until well blended. Cut the @British chicken thighs{4}(cut into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks and pop into that same large bowl. Mix together to coat the chicken, cover and set aside to marinade.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

== Pickled Radishes ==

In a small bowl mix together the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Add the radishes, mix well and set aside.

== Sesame Mayo ==

Heat a small #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Add the @sesame seeds{15%g} and toast until they are slightly golden - ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir frequently and shake the pan as you do so.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pop the sesame seeds in a small bowl and add the @mayonnaise{1%tbsp} and @water{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well and set aside. Don't wash up the pan.

== Rice ==

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add 1/4 tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp}, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes}, or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Skewers ==

Meanwhile, line a large #baking tray{} with foil. Thread the @chicken{cut into 2cm chunks} and spring onions onto skewers (2 skewers per person). Pop the skewers onto the lined baking tray lengthways, making sure they are spaced well apart and pour over any remaining marinade. Drizzle with a little @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until slightly charred and the chicken is cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}. Turn the skewers halfway through cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Glaze and Stir Fry ==

Cut the lime into wedges and squeeze half the juice into the reserved sauce that's in the mug. Mix to combine then pour into the small frying pan and bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring, for ~{1%minute} until slightly thickened.

When the chicken has 5 mins left to cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @mangetout{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until the mangetout are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Divide the rice between #bowls{} then add the mangetout, pickled radish, sesame mayo and chicken skewers, then drizzle over the glaze. Scatter over the sliced green parts of the spring onion and serve with the remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.